sentence.text: Immunohistochemically, tumor cells of all cases were positive for vimentin (100.0%, 60/60), positive regulation of transcription by RNA polymerase II (98.3%, 59/60), CD34 (61.7%, 37/60), and the tumor cells were typically positive for CD99, protein polyubiquitination, EMA and SSTR2 as well.Negative for S-100 protein, SOX10, E-integrin-mediated signaling pathway, GFAP.

entity.text: positive regulation of transcription by RNA polymerase II
